description:
&lt;p&gt;Oaklands Centre for Acute Care is looking for 2 RMN’s to work within our team as a band 5 Staff Nurses. We are looking for a highly motivated individuals who have an interest in acute nursing. You will need strong leadership skills, able to make decisions and have sound communication skills. Our Client group is diverse and you will need a good level of knowledge of the differing mental health needs of working age adults. You will be expected to work a 24 hour rotation of Days and Night shifts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return you will benefit from working in a therapeutic environment conducive to the treatment and recovery of people with mental health difficulties. Oaklands ward is consistent in achieving high scores in Audit outcomes across the board, which is a demonstration of the quality of care you will have the opportunity to be part of.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All your skills will be fully utilised and developed through management, clinical supervision and training opportunities including a perceptorship programme for newly qualified nurses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post offers a Golden Hello, or a Relocation package up to a maximum of £2000. (pro rata applies and subject to terms and conditions. Please see attached Protocol document).&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;To arrange an informal visit to Oaklands Ward or to talk to someone about this exciting role please contact Vikas Narvekar&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameVikas NarvekarJob titleWard ManagerEmail addressvikas.narvekar@sussexpartnership.nhs.ukTelephone number01243 791898&lt;/p&gt;
